-- European Stocks Decline as Greece, Portugal Fall; U.S. Index Futures Slip
-- Andrew Rummer
-- 2010-06-24T07:33:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/european-stocks-fall-for-third-day-greece-portugal-spain-lead-retreat.html

          
          
             European stocks fell, erasing
earlier gains, as shares in Greece, Portugal and Spain led
declines.  
 The Stoxx Europe 600 Index dropped 0.3 percent to 253.62 at
8:32 a.m. in London, having earlier risen as much as 0.4
percent.  
          
          


  


        